about.summary: Generate simple tables in terminals from a nested list of strings.

name: terminaltables
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set name = "terminaltables" %}
{% set version = "3.1.0" %}
{% set sha256 = 'f3eb0eb92e3833972ac36796293ca0906e998dc3be91fbe1f8615b331b853b81' %}

package:
  name: {{ name|lower }}
  version: {{ version }}

source:
  fn: {{ name }}-{{ version }}.tar.gz
  url: https://pypi.io/packages/source/{{ name[0] }}/{{ name }}/{{ name }}-{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: {{ sha256 }}

build:
  noarch: python
  number: 0
  script: python setup.py install --single-version-externally-managed --record record.txt

requirements:
  build:
    - python
    - setuptools
  run:
    - python
    - colorama
    - termcolor

test:
  imports:
    - terminaltables

about:
  home: https://robpol86.github.io/terminaltables
  license: MIT
  license_family: MIT
  # xref : https://github.com/Robpol86/terminaltables/pull/49
  # license_file: LICENSE
  summary: Generate simple tables in terminals from a nested list of strings.
  doc_url: https://robpol86.github.io/terminaltables
  dev_url: https://github.com/Robpol86/terminaltables

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - mariusvniekerk
